text: I’ve been coming here for Malay food, and it used to be really good. However, I was a bit disappointed today. The lontong was diluted and lacked flavor, the potato cutlet was cold and hard, barely tasted like potato, and the chicken wing was cold and soggy.

Date of visit: 29 July 23
Time of visit: 0950H
Nearest MRT: NIL
Items ordered: mee rebus add bergedil
Total damage: SG$3.50
Payment: cash and digital
Taste: good
Service: self
How: You find your own seat, you queue, you order, they make, you pay and collect, you bring back to your seat, you take pic, you eat, you clear, you go.
Pros: cheap and good
Cons: no aircon, expect to queue, may not be easy to find seat
Will eat again: yes

Consistency is somewhat still there.

Taste good, just remember the broth to be thicker.

It’s long queue on weekend so I got curious.

However I find all the fried food too oily and the chilli are more sweet than spicy

Didn’t enjoy and it’s quite pricey to add cuttlefish alone as $2

This has the best Lontong that I know of. For $3, I get rice cake, tofu, hard boiled egg and sayur lodeh with cabbage, carrot and french beans.

Mildly spicy, right level of lemak and complete with the sweet sambal chilly that atop the dish. Perfect for breakfast!
